.TH TEXTMIDIFORMEDIT 1 2026-07-09 "Linux" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
TextMidiFormEdit.py \- Design a form for 
.B textmidicgm
to turn into a random musical work as a 
.B textmidi
file as a 
.B textmidi
file.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.SY TextMidiFormEdit.py
.OP OPTION
.OP INPUT
.YS

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B TextMidiFormEdit.py
converts a text file description of 
a MIDI file to a binary standard MIDI file.
.B TextMidiFormEdit.py 
is fully documented in a PDF file TextMidiFormEdit.pdf.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-TextMidiFormEdit.py\  XML_form_file
The input file: a boost::serialization XML archive file for a form definition.
.
.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.
The
.B TextMidiFormEdit.py
program always returns EXIT_SUCCESS.
.SH ERRORS
.
